What are the iPad mini specs?     The iPad provided is a 64GB iPad mini 3 with retina display and equipped with wifi. You also receive AppleCare+ for iPad, which provides repair or replacement coverage (both parts and labor) from Apple-authorized technicians.     How do I set up my iPad?   Please contact DEI Support  and request a Quick Start guide.         What is AirWatch?  AirWatch provides mobile device management (MDM) across an enterprise. It is through AirWatch that we are offering a NYULMC-specific profile with recommended applications and webclips. AirWatch also allows MCIT to configure and update device settings over-the-air, enforce security policies , and remotely wipe managed devices by request in case of loss or theft.    Can MCIT monitor my device usage and access my data through AirWatch?    MCIT and DEI will have very limited and specific usage about your device through AirWatch. It tracks:     Who enrolled in AirWatch   The serial number of your iPad mini   Which apps you chose to install from the recommended catalog only   It  does not  do location tracking and it  cannot  access your email, contacts, browsing history, or your photos on your iPad. AirWatch does not receive information about other apps you choose to download and install outside of the NYULMC app catalog.       Though enrollment in AirWatch is optional, we strongly recommend you enroll in order to take full advantage of this program during your clinical experiences. [Please refer to iPad Usage Policy for more information.]            Does AirWatch impact the performance of my iPad?   It does not have any significant impact on the performance of your device nor the battery life.     Does my device "talk" to AirWatch?  When connected to wireless internet, the device intermittently communicates with AirWatch mobile device management that it is online. When online, the device does a daily check of the application inventory. If new items are available in the catalog or NYULMC apps are updated, AirWatch will conduct that update in the background and you will receive an alert on your iPad. No other information about your device or usage is communicated.    I didn’t initially add a passcode when I set up my iPad but now my device requires a passcode. Why?   NYULMC mobile standard policy requires that your device has a passcode . Please keep in mind that your passcode is not associated with your Kerberos. Neither DEI nor MCIT have access to this passcode. Please be sure to select a sequence of characters that is meaningful to you.   Epic isn’t working! How can I fix this?   First, please ensure that you have followed the configuration procedure for Epic Canto on your device. If that does not resolve the issue, please contact DEI Support .   My device asks me for my Exchange password. What is that and why is it yielding an error?   Your Exchange password is the password to your Kerberos account. If this yields an error, you simply have not requested access for your e-mail to be synced to a smart device. Please submit a ticket via the MCIT Service Catalog . MCIT will respond to your ticket and attach a Mobile Device Consent Form  for your review. Once MCIT receives an e-mail from you confirming receipt and consent, your account will then be assigned ActiveSync privileges and you will be able to sync your e-mail to smart devices.   I'd prefer not to sync my official NYULMC e-mail to my device. Is there a way to disable the automatic prompt every time I click on the e-mail icon?     If you'd rather not connect your device to NYULMC e-mail and you  do not want to see the e-mail password prompts, you can perform the following:   Open up the Settings app. Tap General. Tap Profiles (near the bottom). Tap the Configuration Profile named “Prod Exchange ActiveSync” and tap the Remove button.  How can I add my personal e-mail to my iPad?    Click on Settings-->Mail-->Add Account     Do I have to use this device?    This is your personal iPad. However, it is expected that an iPad will be utilized during your clinical experience. We hope that it proves useful and informs your clinical experience.        Whom do I contact regarding any questions or concerns that I might have?    Please do not hesitate to contact DEI Support for any reason, whether it’s a technological issue, an app recommendation, or your general feedback. We appreciate hearing from you! What are the iPad mini specs?     The iPad provided is a 64GB iPad mini 3 with retina display and equipped with wifi. You also receive AppleCare+ for iPad, which provides repair or replacement coverage (both parts and labor) from Apple-authorized technicians.     How do I set up my iPad?   Please contact DEI Support  and request a Quick Start guide.         What is AirWatch?  AirWatch provides mobile device management (MDM) across an enterprise. It is through AirWatch that we are offering a NYULMC-specific profile with recommended applications and webclips. AirWatch also allows MCIT to configure and update device settings over-the-air, enforce security policies , and remotely wipe managed devices by request in case of loss or theft.    Can MCIT monitor my device usage and access my data through AirWatch?    MCIT and DEI will have very limited and specific usage about your device through AirWatch. It tracks:     Who enrolled in AirWatch   The serial number of your iPad mini   Which apps you chose to install from the recommended catalog only   It  does not  do location tracking and it  cannot  access your email, contacts, browsing history, or your photos on your iPad. AirWatch does not receive information about other apps you choose to download and install outside of the NYULMC app catalog.       Though enrollment in AirWatch is optional, we strongly recommend you enroll in order to take full advantage of this program during your clinical experiences. [Please refer to iPad Usage Policy for more information.]            Does AirWatch impact the performance of my iPad?   It does not have any significant impact on the performance of your device nor the battery life.     Does my device "talk" to AirWatch?  When connected to wireless internet, the device intermittently communicates with AirWatch mobile device management that it is online. When online, the device does a daily check of the application inventory. If new items are available in the catalog or NYULMC apps are updated, AirWatch will conduct that update in the background and you will receive an alert on your iPad. No other information about your device or usage is communicated.    I didn’t initially add a passcode when I set up my iPad but now my device requires a passcode. Why?   NYULMC mobile standard policy requires that your device has a passcode . Please keep in mind that your passcode is not associated with your Kerberos. Neither DEI nor MCIT have access to this passcode. Please be sure to select a sequence of characters that is meaningful to you.   Epic isn’t working! How can I fix this?   First, please ensure that you have followed the configuration procedure for Epic Canto on your device. If that does not resolve the issue, please contact DEI Support .   My device asks me for my Exchange password. What is that and why is it yielding an error?   Your Exchange password is the password to your Kerberos account. If this yields an error, you simply have not requested access for your e-mail to be synced to a smart device. Please submit a ticket via the MCIT Service Catalog . MCIT will respond to your ticket and attach a Mobile Device Consent Form  for your review. Once MCIT receives an e-mail from you confirming receipt and consent, your account will then be assigned ActiveSync privileges and you will be able to sync your e-mail to smart devices.   I'd prefer not to sync my official NYULMC e-mail to my device. Is there a way to disable the automatic prompt every time I click on the e-mail icon?     If you'd rather not connect your device to NYULMC e-mail and you  do not want to see the e-mail password prompts, you can perform the following:   Open up the Settings app. Tap General. Tap Profiles (near the bottom). Tap the Configuration Profile named “Prod Exchange ActiveSync” and tap the Remove button.  How can I add my personal e-mail to my iPad?    Click on Settings-->Mail-->Add Account     Do I have to use this device?    This is your personal iPad. However, it is expected that an iPad will be utilized during your clinical experience. We hope that it proves useful and informs your clinical experience.        Whom do I contact regarding any questions or concerns that I might have?    Please do not hesitate to contact DEI Support for any reason, whether it’s a technological issue, an app recommendation, or your general feedback. We appreciate hearing from you!
